OL,7,FShe said: "We inherited a #22 billion
OL,8,Fblackhole from the previous government
OL,9,Fwho made unfunded spending commitments
OL,10,Fwith no idea how to pay them.
OL,12,F"When I became chancellor I took an
OL,13,Fimmediate audit of the spending
OL,14,Fsituation to understand the scale of
OL,15,Fthat challenge, and I made difficult
OL,16,Fdecisions to put the public finances
OL,17,Fon a sustainable footing.
OL,19,F"They were tough decisions, but they
OL,20,Fwere the right decisions."
